The continuous random variable \(X\) follows the distribution shown by the density curve and spinner below. It has a mean of \(\mu_{X}=53.6\) and standard deviation of \(\sigma_{X}=9.03\).



That spinner (\(X\)) will be fairly spun 865 times, and the sample mean of the spins will be recorded. Determine the probability that the random sample mean is more than 53.66. \[P\left(\bar{X}>53.66\right) ~=~ \,? \]

Please approximate the random mean as a normal distribution with parameters suggested by the central limit theorem.
